  <chapter id="generaltest"><title>General Orca Functionality</title>

    <para>The tests in this section are meant to test general Orca
      functionality that should be work regardless of the application
      in use.</para>

    <section id="interoperabilitytest"><title>Interaction with Other ATs</title>
      <para>The tests in this section are to ensure that Orca does not
        can adverse effects on other assistive technologies that may be
	running, and that other assitive technologies do not adversely 
	effect Orca.</para>

    </section>

    <section id="flatreviewtest"><title>Flat Review</title>

      <para>The tests in this section are to ensure that the Orca flat
        review functionality is working as expected.  This includes
	making sure the various keystrokes work and produce the
	desired results.</para>

    </section>

    <section id="learnmodetest"><title>Learn Mode</title>

      <para>The tests in this section are to ensure that the Orca
        Learn Mode functionality works as expected for both the
        keyboard and braille, including entering and exiting Learn
        Mode.</para>

    </section>

    <section id="whereamitest"><title>Where Am I?</title>

      <para>The tests in this section are to ensure that the Orca
        Where Am I functionality produces the desired
        information.</para>

    </section>

    <section id="sayalltest"><title>Say All</title>

      <para>The tests in this section are to ensure that the Orca Say
        All functionality behaves appropriately for contiguous
        document content, including GEdit, StarOffice, etc.  The Say
        All tests for flat review of dialogs are in the Flat Review
        section.</para>

    </section>

    <section id="verbalizedpunctest"><title>Verbalized Punctuation</title>

      <para>The tests in this section are to ensure that the Orca
        Verbalized Punctuation functionality provides the desired 
	output for the various verbalized punctuation settings.</para>

    </section>

    <section id="verbalizedlinktest"><title>Verbalized Links</title>

      <para>The tests in this section are to ensure that the Orca
        Verbalized Link functionality provides the desired 
	output for the various verbalized link settings.</para>

    </section>

    <section id="verbalizedcapstest"><title>Verbalized Caps</title>

      <para>The tests in this section are to ensure that the Orca
        Verbalized Caps functionality provides the desired output for
        the various verbalized capitalization settings.</para>

    </section>

    <section id="spellingmodetest"><title>Spelling Mode</title>

      <para>The tests in this section are to ensure that the Orca
        Spelling Mode functionality provides the desired output for
        the various spelling mode settings.</para>

    </section>

    <section id="textattributestest"><title>Text Attributes</title>

      <para>The tests in this section are to ensure that Orca
        accurately provides text attribute (e.g., font, bolding, etc.)
        information when requested by the user.</para>

    </section>

    <section id="keywordechotest"><title>Key and Word Echo</title>

      <para>The tests in this section are to ensure that Orca works
        accurately with the various key and word echo settings.</para>

      <section><title>Simple Typing of Words</title>
        <para>&tgoal; Orca should speak words as they are typed.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Type a line of 10 words each followed by spaces.</para>
        <para>&tresult; When the space is typed after each word, the word should be spoken.</para>
      </section>
      <section><title>Typing Words with Punctuation</title>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if orca speaks the word when a boundary is reached.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; type a line of 10 words, the first 5 followed by a period and the second 5 followed by a comma.</para>
        <para>&tresult; When the period or comma is typed the word should be spoken.  When a space is typed after the punctuation mark the word should not be spoken again.</para>
      </section>
    </section>

    <section id="brailletest"><title>Braille</title>

      <para>The tests in this section are to make sure that Orca does
        the right thing with respect to spaces and indentation on the
	braille display and with respect to the various braille 
	spacing and indentation settings.</para>

    </section>
  </chapter>

